<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4732.1.4>
    bibo:endPage "116" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-02-11" ;
    bibo:startPage "99" ;
    bibo:volume "4732" ;
    dc:creator "Colpani, Daniara; Benetti, César João; Hamada, Neusa; Andrade-Souza, Vanderly; Schoeninger, Karine; Michat, Mariano C." ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Description of the immature stages of the Neotropical whirligig beetle Gyrinus (Neogyrinus) rozei Ochs, 1953 (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae) and first report of the parasitoid wasp Melanosmicra sp. (Hymenoptera: Chalcididae) on a Gyrinus species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662595>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662597>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662599>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662601>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662603>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662605>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662607> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662595>
    dc:description "FIGURES 4–6. Eggs of Gyrinus rozei. 4. Dorsal view, first day. 5. Dorsal view, fifth day. 6. Eggs on the substrate. Scale bars 0.2 mm (Figs 4, 5) and 2.0 mm (Fig. 6)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662595/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662597>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–10. Eggs of Gyrinus rozei analyzed under scanning electron microscopy. 7. Dorsal view. 8. Micropyle (anterior pole). 9. Dorsal region amplified showing details of cells of chorion with superficial circular grooves. 10. Lateral region showing chorion details. Scale bars 200 µm (Fig. 7), 20 µm (Figs 8, 9) and 50 µm (Fig. 10)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662597/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662599>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–13. Gyrinus rozei larvae. 11. Dorsal habitus, first-instar. 12. Dorsal habitus, second-instar. 13. Dorsal habitus, third-instar. Scale bars 0.5 mm (Fig. 11), 2.0 mm (Figs 12, 13)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662599/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662601>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–15. Gyrinus rozei, first-instar larva, cephalic capsule. 14. Dorsal view. 15. Ventral view. Numbers and lowercase letters indicate primary setae and pores. Note: frontoclypeus (FR), parietal (PA) and egg bursters (EB). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662601/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662603>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–22. Gyrinus rozei, first-instar larva. 16. Right antenna, dorsal view. 17. Left antenna, ventral view. 18. Right maxilla, dorsal view. 19. Left maxilla, ventral view. 20. Labium, dorsal view. 21. Labium, ventral view. 22. Right mandible, dorsal view. Numbers and lowercase letters indicate primary setae and pores. Note: antenna (AN), labium (LA), mandible (MN), maxilla (MX). Scale bars 0.1 mm (Figs 18, 19, 22), 0.3 mm (Figs1 6, 17, 20, 21)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662603/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662605>
    dc:description "FIGURES 23–26. Gyrinus rozei, first-instar larva. 23. Left metathoracic leg, anterior view. 24. Right metathoracic leg, posterior view. 25. Abdominal segment X and hooks, ventral view. 26. Abdominal segment X and hooks, lateral view. Scale bars 0.3 mm (Figs 25, 26), 0.5 mm (Figs 23, 24)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662605/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3662607>
    dc:description "FIGURES 27–28. Gyrinus rozei, pupa. 27. Ventral habitus. 28. Dorsal habitus. Scale bars 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3662607/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

